modules.description: This module provides a comparison function for S-expression strings, enabling lexicographic ordering of values of type `Sexp_string_quickcheck.Sexp_string.t`. It supports direct comparison between two such values, returning an integer indicating their relative ordering. This is useful in contexts like sorting or implementing ordered collections where S-expressions need to be compared directly.

This module defines a string type for use with S-expressions and QuickCheck testing. It provides functions to generate, observe, and shrink string values for property-based testing, along with conversion to S-expressions. It is used to test functions that process string atoms in S-expression formats.

This module defines a string-based type for S-expressions with support for QuickCheck-style property testing, including generation, observation, and shrinking of test values. It provides direct conversion to S-expressions and a comparison module for lexicographic ordering. Concrete use cases include testing parsers, serializers, and other functions that consume or produce S-expressions.

This module provides string types tailored for S-expression handling and QuickCheck testing. It includes functions for generating, observing, and shrinking string values, along with direct conversion to S-expressions and lexicographic comparison. It is used to test parsers, serializers, and functions that process string atoms or S-expressions.
